The '''1978 Monte Carlo Open''' was a men's [[tennis]] tournament played on [[Clay court|outdoor clay courts]] at the [[Monte Carlo Country Club]] in [[Monte Carlo]], [[Monaco]] . The tournament was part of the [[World Championship Tennis|WCT Tour]], which was incorporated into the [[1978 Colgate-Palmolive Grand Prix]] circuit. It was the 72nd edition of the event and was held from 10 April through 16 April 1978. [[Raúl Ramírez]], the no. 5 seed, won the singles title.
==Champions== ===Singles=== {{flagicon|MEX}} '''[[Raúl Ramírez]]''' defeated {{flagicon|TCH}} [[Tomáš Šmíd]] 6–3, 6–3, 6–4
===Doubles=== {{flagicon|USA}} '''[[Peter Fleming (tennis)|Peter Fleming]]''' / {{flagicon|TCH}} '''[[Tomáš Šmíd]]''' defeated {{flagicon|CHI}} [[Jaime Fillol]] / {{flagicon|ROM|1965}} [[Ilie Năstase]] 6–4, 7–5
