'''Bantowbol''' or '''bantubol''' is a style of [[music of Cameroon|music]] from [[Cameroon]]. The genre is derived from Cameroonian folk music. The name ''bantowbol'' is partially derived from ''bal'', a term for [[accordion]] playing. The principal musicians of bantowbol are [[Gibraltar Drakus]] and [[Nkondo Si Tony]].

