The '''Español en Toledo''' (Spanish in Toledo) Program is an initiative of the University of [[Castile-La Mancha]] General Foundation, aimed at teaching and promoting the [[Spanish language]] and culture among students from all over the world, while using the city of Toledo (Spain) as a classroom, due to its many monuments and historical sites. Currently, the program works with several American universities, such as the [[University of North Dakota]] or [[Ohio University]] at Athens, organizing Study Abroad Programs for their students.

