The '''genevoise''' was the short-lived currency of [[Geneva]] between 1794 and 1795. It was subdivided into 10 ''decimes'' (singular: ''decimi''). The genevoise replaced and was replaced by the [[Geneva thaler|thaler]].

==Coins==
In 1794, silver coins were issued in denominations of ½ and 1 decimi and 1 genevoise.

