'''''Gába''''' is a bilingual [[Sámi]] [[magazine]] that is published six times a year by the Sámi women's forum [[Sami Nisson Forum]] and that has funds earmarked for it in the annual budget of the [[Sami Parliament of Norway]]. The magazine was published for the first time on [[International Women's Day]] (March 8) in 1996.<ref>{{cite web |title= Gába - Áigečála guovtti gillii - sáme- ja dárogillii (Gába - a bilingual magazine - Northern Sámi and Norwegian|url= http://www.saminissonforum.org/gaba/ |date= |work=Sami Nisson Forum|accessdate=28 June 2009|language=Northern Sami}}</ref> Although the main languages are [[Norwegian language|Norwegian]] and [[Northern Sámi]], articles are occasionally written in [[Southern Sámi]], [[Lule Sámi]] and [[Swedish language|Swedish]]. The articles mainly deal with the everyday life of the Sámi from a woman's perspective.<ref>{{cite web|title= Sámi Culture in the Nordic Countries – Administration, Support, Evaluation|url= http://www.utexas.edu/courses/sami/dieda/hist/nordic.htm|author=Gaski, Harald and Tr. John Weinstock|work=University of Texas|accessdate=28 June 2009}}</ref> 

