{{Infobox television channel | name = Sky 3D (Germany) | logofile = Sky 3D DE Logo 2015.png | logosize = | logocaption = | logoalt = | logo2 = | launch = {{Start date and age|2010|10|13|df=y}} | closed date = {{End date and age|2017|7|31|df=y}} | picture format = [[1080i]] ([[3D television|3DTV]]) | share = | share as of = | share source = | network = [[Sky Deutschland]] | owner = [[Sky Deutschland|Sky Deutschland AG]] | parent = | slogan = | motto = | country = | language = [[German language|German]] | broadcast area = [[Germany]], [[Austria]] | affiliates = | headquarters = [[Unterföhring]], [[Germany]] | former names = | replaced names = | replaced by names = | sister names = | timeshift names = | website = {{URL|www.sky.de/3d}} | terr serv 1 = | terr chan 1 = | sat serv 1 = | sat chan 1 = | cable serv 1 = | cable chan 1 = | sat radio serv 1 = | sat radio chan 1 = | iptv serv 1 = | iptv chan 1 = | online serv 1 = | online chan 1 = | 3gmobile serv 1 = }}
'''Sky 3D''' was a television channel of [[Sky Deutschland]] that lasted from 2010 to 2017. It only broadcast [[3D television|3D]] content.<ref>{{cite web|title=Sky startet 3D-Angebot im Oktober 2010|url=http://info.sky.de/inhalt/de/medienzentrum_news_uk_02092010.jsp|website=sky.de|accessdate=12 January 2018|date=2 September 2010}}</ref>
==History== Sky 3D launched on October 13, 2010 via [[Astra 19.2°E]] and cable operator [[Kabel BW]] in regular operation, prior to a test broadcast. The transmitter was free for all customers for 3 months. Since then, the was made available free of charge. The broadcasting time was usually between 11 and 24 o'clock, while in the broadcast-free time, trailers were shown. From summer 2013, a one-time activation fee of € 29.90 was required to access the channel. Sky 3D was discontinued on July 1, 2017 due to its low ratings.<ref>{{cite web|title=Sky startet 3D-Angebot im Oktober 2010|url=https://www.broadbandtvnews.com/2017/06/27/sky-deutschland-scraps-sky-3d-and-sky-hd-fan-zone/|website=Broadband TV News}}</ref>
